snippet: Early voting results indicated Sunday that Leonid Tibilov, a K.G.B. veteran, had been elected president of South Ossetia after a protracted election struggle that Moscow had hoped to avoid.
abstract: Early results from a fourth round of voting in South Ossetia, a breakaway region in Georgia, indicate that the former KGB official Leonid Tibilov has been elected president, bringing an end to a long, tumultuous campaign season that proved an embarrassment to Moscow, the region’s source of military and financial support.
lead_paragraph: Early voting results indicated Sunday that Leonid Tibilov, a K.G.B. veteran, had been elected president of South Ossetia after a protracted election struggle that Moscow had hoped to avoid.

headline.seo: Ex-K.G.B. Official Said to Win South Ossetia Presidency
headline.main: Ex-K.G.B. Agent Said to Win South Ossetia Presidency
headline.print_headline: Ex-K.G.B. Official Leads Vote for South Ossetia President
